Class TestReport

  • java.lang.Object
    • test.TestReport
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    class TestReport
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Individual test report.

    This class contains fields and convenience methods related to the result of running a single test. It is used internally by Series to pass test results. For failed tests, it is returned in SeriesReport objects.

      • successful

        boolean successful()

      • fatal

        boolean fatal()
        Returns true if and only if the test stopped with a fatal error, or cleanup stopped with any error (all cleanup erros are fatal).

      • print

        void print(PrintStream stream)
        Prints a report for a failed test.

        The test name is printed. If the main test failed, then the reason for the failure is printed. The task being performed during the failure is shown, if there was one. If the failure was not a timeout, the stack trace is shown as well. If the cleanup task failed, a description of the error and a stack trace are printed.

        Parameters:
        stream - Stream to receive the formatted test report.
